@marmbrus, Thank you for your comments.
Modified to use `withNullability`.

And no problem, because exact types and nullability is important for my project.

when  numPartitioner is set to 0, HashPartitioner would not be failed ,because getPartition method would not be called.

here is the DAGScheduler's code

```
if (partitions.size == 0) {
  return new JobWaiter[U](this, jobId, 0, resultHandler)
}
```

if partitionSize is 0, job does not really submit.  this is why i set it to 0
